1
00:01:50,020 --> 00:01:56,100
=Later, I Laughed=

2
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:02,540
(Four days ago)

3
00:02:02,540 --> 00:02:03,570
Give me the rod.

4
00:02:04,540 --> 00:02:06,340
Hold on. Don't you see I'm busy?

5
00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:09,540
- What rod?
- You hang it yourself.

6
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:13,160
I just finished
washing the bowls for you.

7
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,550
And now you're making me work again.

8
00:02:14,550 --> 00:02:16,070
What do you mean
by helping me wash the bowls?

9
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:17,380
Then who am I helping?

10
00:02:17,460 --> 00:02:19,170
Don't use bowls
when you eat in the future.

11
00:02:19,820 --> 00:02:21,140
This way there's no need to help.

12
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:23,540
Also, don't wear clothes anymore.

13
00:02:23,540 --> 00:02:25,700
So I won't have to wash them
for you if they get dirty.

14
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,960
And after washing them,
I still have to hang them for you.

15
00:02:29,340 --> 00:02:30,540
Are you crazy?

16
00:02:33,140 --> 00:02:34,700
You're the one who's crazy.

17
00:02:48,380 --> 00:02:49,540
Why are you just getting back?

18
00:02:52,420 --> 00:02:54,260
Didn't you say to
cook pork chop soup tonight?

19
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:57,020
It's already 5:30 PM.
Is there still time?

20
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:58,860
It takes an hour just to defrost.

21
00:02:59,260 --> 00:03:00,760
We won't be able to eat at 6:30 PM.

22
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,040
Why are you just coming back now?

23
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:03,140
What were you doing all afternoon?

24
00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:04,500
There is no reason.

25
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:06,020
Are you going to eat or not?

26
00:03:06,510 --> 00:03:08,340
I've been waiting all afternoon
and I didn't get angry.

27
00:03:08,340 --> 00:03:09,500
But now you get mad.

28
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,700
Who asked you to wait?

29
00:03:10,700 --> 00:03:11,860
You have hands and feet.

30
00:03:11,860 --> 00:03:14,020
Couldn't you take
the chops out to defrost?

31
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:17,140
- I...
- You wanted pork chop soup.

32
00:03:17,300 --> 00:03:19,500
You didn't know the chops were here?

33
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:21,300
It's been all afternoon.

34
00:03:21,300 --> 00:03:22,980
You just sit on the sofa.

35
00:03:23,020 --> 00:03:24,560
Can't you get up from the sofa,

36
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:26,330
walk over here and
open the refrigerator door

37
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:27,860
to take out the chops to defrost?

38
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:30,020
I don't even need to look to know.

39
00:03:30,260 --> 00:03:32,860
You just sit on the sofa
and look at your phone.

40
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:35,700
If you forget and
you are too lazy to do it,

41
00:03:35,700 --> 00:03:37,020
just say sorry to me.

42
00:03:37,420 --> 00:03:38,820
Is it so hard to say sorry?

43
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:42,500
Do you think your life is going too well

44
00:03:42,500 --> 00:03:43,580
and we have to fight?

45
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,820
My life is really going too well.

46
00:03:55,420 --> 00:03:56,700
Are you crazy?

47
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:09,460
(Quarrels with her husband
day after day,)

48
00:04:09,660 --> 00:04:11,340
(despair over the mundane life,)

49
00:04:11,620 --> 00:04:13,020
(and the illness known)

50
00:04:13,020 --> 00:04:14,460
(only to herself until now)

51
00:04:14,900 --> 00:04:16,540
(make Li Dongmei feel suffocated.)

52
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:19,180
(She decided to embark on)

53
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:21,060
(a spontaneous runaway from home.)

54
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:25,860
(The next day,)

55
00:04:26,220 --> 00:04:27,860
(the unsuspecting Xiuya's dad)

56
00:04:27,860 --> 00:04:29,180
(woke up from his sleep,)

57
00:04:29,540 --> 00:04:30,900
(only to find a scene of)

58
00:04:30,900 --> 00:04:32,780
(a bloody incident
triggered by frozen chops.)

59
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:48,820
(Shanghai Hongqiao Station)

60
00:05:05,900 --> 00:05:06,740
Hello.

61
00:05:07,900 --> 00:05:09,060
Did I get the wrong door?

62
00:05:09,260 --> 00:05:10,220
Who are you looking for?

63
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:12,300
This is Room 201, Building 3, right?

64
00:05:12,340 --> 00:05:16,860
=Episode 20=

65
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:20,660
Now please imagine yourself as a tree.

66
00:05:21,060 --> 00:05:22,660
Your feet begin to take root,

67
00:05:22,660 --> 00:05:24,340
deeply embedding into the soil.

68
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:26,460
As you embrace this tree,

69
00:05:26,460 --> 00:05:28,860
the tree is also embracing you.

70
00:05:29,660 --> 00:05:30,810
Its energy continuously flows

71
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:33,900
into you through ophryon.

72
00:05:35,340 --> 00:05:37,060
Yes, the ophryon is here.

73
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:48,460
Why don't I feel anything?

74
00:05:50,220 --> 00:05:51,860
Try to feel it carefully.

75
00:05:52,060 --> 00:05:53,220
This is called Tree Therapy.

76
00:05:53,340 --> 00:05:54,780
You are lazy every day.

77
00:05:54,780 --> 00:05:56,420
I think you should
hug a tree every day.

78
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,660
I don't think you can do it.

79
00:05:59,980 --> 00:06:01,060
If I can't do it, can you?

80
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:02,460
Yeah, I can do it, and you can't.

81
00:06:02,460 --> 00:06:03,780
I can't do it and you can. No.

82
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:04,780
I can do it and you...

83
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:07,620
What are we even talking about?

84
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:12,100
Come on. I'll teach you a secret.

85
00:06:13,100 --> 00:06:13,940
What is it?

86
00:06:14,260 --> 00:06:15,190
Come on. Stand properly.

87
00:06:17,420 --> 00:06:18,260
Just feel it.

88
00:06:30,060 --> 00:06:30,900
How is it?

89
00:06:31,460 --> 00:06:33,460
The unique Shi's Therapy.

90
00:06:33,620 --> 00:06:34,540
Do you feel

91
00:06:34,540 --> 00:06:36,900
that I'm transferring energy into
your body right now?

92
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:38,900
You're so childish.

93
00:06:52,860 --> 00:06:53,780
Are you asleep?

94
00:06:54,420 --> 00:06:55,460
I didn't fall asleep.

95
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:57,100
I even heard you snoring.

96
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,300
You're hearing things.

97
00:07:00,180 --> 00:07:01,100
Alright, let me go.

98
00:07:01,540 --> 00:07:03,460
No, I haven't finished transferring yet.

99
00:07:04,780 --> 00:07:06,100
They are watching us.

100
00:07:07,060 --> 00:07:08,180
Alright, just watch it then.

101
00:07:10,620 --> 00:07:11,460
By the way,

102
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:12,980
you can call me now.

103
00:07:13,420 --> 00:07:15,460
Look. I changed your name.

104
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:19,300
Advertising Department, Shi.

105
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:22,300
Please understand
during this special period.

106
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:23,980
I have a performance later.

107
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:25,340
How about I take you back now?

108
00:07:25,340 --> 00:07:26,420
Where are you performing?

109
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,180
You're not on the schedule
at Banghe today.

110
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:29,540
Not at Banghe.

111
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:30,860
In an informal site.

112
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:32,780
Are you upset?

113
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,180
Why should I be upset? Let's go.

114
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:43,300
Thank you.

115
00:07:48,540 --> 00:07:49,380
Thank you.

116
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:59,180
(Second Affiliated Hospital
of Hujiang Medical University)

117
00:08:06,540 --> 00:08:08,420
I feel Shi Ye is a bit upset.

118
00:08:08,490 --> 00:08:09,340
But if I don't say it,

119
00:08:09,340 --> 00:08:11,420
my mom will eventually
get suspicious.

120
00:08:11,620 --> 00:08:12,460
Actually,

121
00:08:13,620 --> 00:08:14,860
it's better to confess earlier.

122
00:08:15,780 --> 00:08:18,300
Now everything is piled up together.

123
00:08:19,780 --> 00:08:20,620
In fact,

124
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:23,540
it would have been better
if you said this a few days earlier.

125
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:24,420
You see,

126
00:08:24,420 --> 00:08:26,780
aren't all best friends
Monday morning quarterbacks?

127
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:27,620
That's true.

128
00:08:28,460 --> 00:08:29,460
Actually,

129
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:32,580
I'm curious to see how long
you can hold on.

130
00:08:32,580 --> 00:08:34,580
Why don't you hold on a bit longer?

131
00:08:35,060 --> 00:08:36,900
Let's see when the truth will come out.

132
00:08:37,180 --> 00:08:38,300
We'll be with you unconditionally.

133
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:39,580
Of course, absolutely.

134
00:08:39,580 --> 00:08:40,440
Full support.

135
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:41,420
That's a must.

136
00:08:41,420 --> 00:08:42,300
Truly loyal.

137
00:08:42,300 --> 00:08:43,300
Stop interrupting, guys.

138
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:44,940
I just want to find
the right opportunity

139
00:08:44,940 --> 00:08:46,060
to confess to my mom.

140
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:48,580
The key is how to make her
feel less uncomfortable

141
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:49,580
and not too sad.

142
00:08:52,950 --> 00:08:54,520
Easily accepted.

143
00:08:55,180 --> 00:08:57,180
And don't be too sad.

144
00:08:59,780 --> 00:09:00,900
I have a method.

145
00:09:03,540 --> 00:09:04,550
Forget it. I won't say it.

146
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:06,060
- Say it.
- Say it.

147
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:08,780
Playing cat and mouse, you know?

148
00:09:09,540 --> 00:09:10,540
A very famous idiom.

149
00:09:10,540 --> 00:09:12,300
You understand
playing cat and mouse, right?

150
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:15,300
First, give Auntie something shocking.

151
00:09:15,900 --> 00:09:19,060
Just tell her you're pregnant
with your leader's child.

152
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,780
The company found out.

153
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:22,980
And the leader also
wants to abandon you.

154
00:09:23,060 --> 00:09:24,540
Now you're seven months pregnant.

155
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:26,940
You've already prepared
to be a single mom.

156
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:29,940
As soon as Auntie hears this,
she'll definitely just

157
00:09:30,380 --> 00:09:31,580
faint from anger, right?

158
00:09:31,780 --> 00:09:32,620
Just before Auntie

159
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:34,580
faints from anger,

160
00:09:34,940 --> 00:09:36,300
tell her everything.

161
00:09:36,940 --> 00:09:38,010
What about resignation

162
00:09:38,010 --> 00:09:39,380
or breaking up with your boyfriend,

163
00:09:39,380 --> 00:09:40,480
is that even a big deal?

164
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:42,230
She would definitely
accept them all gladly.

165
00:09:42,230 --> 00:09:43,500
How about it? Isn't it great?

166
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:44,900
I'll take you down first.

167
00:09:44,900 --> 00:09:46,900
I'd like to find something
to hit you with.

168
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,900
You're out of your mind.

169
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:49,740
Do you know

170
00:09:49,900 --> 00:09:52,900
how big a seven-month
pregnant woman's belly is?

171
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:53,740
Explain it to me.

172
00:09:54,540 --> 00:09:55,580
At most three months.

173
00:09:56,540 --> 00:09:59,060
Moreover, is that what you mean
by "playing cat and mouse"?

174
00:09:59,060 --> 00:10:00,940
How did you get into college?

175
00:10:00,940 --> 00:10:01,900
Indeed.

176
00:10:02,060 --> 00:10:03,780
You majored in aquaculture, right?

177
00:10:07,500 --> 00:10:08,470
I said I wouldn't say it,

178
00:10:08,470 --> 00:10:09,580
but you insisted I should.

179
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,330
- I have another one.
- Don't say it.

180
00:10:12,330 --> 00:10:14,060
- No, it's serious.
- Don't say it.

181
00:10:14,060 --> 00:10:16,060
Wait a minute. It's serious.

182
00:10:16,060 --> 00:10:17,500
This time it's serious, no joking.

183
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:19,380
This time, no idioms.

184
00:10:19,380 --> 00:10:21,500
Just a simple word: preparation.

185
00:10:22,940 --> 00:10:25,060
First, test Auntie's attitude.

186
00:10:25,420 --> 00:10:28,180
Just say your colleague,

187
00:10:28,780 --> 00:10:30,580
a certain colleague,

188
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:32,900
who suffered silent treatment
at the company.

189
00:10:33,060 --> 00:10:34,410
He can't take it and he's quitting.

190
00:10:34,820 --> 00:10:36,900
See what Auntie's attitude is
when she hears this.

191
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:39,900
This time, the fish farmer seems
to have a point.

192
00:10:39,900 --> 00:10:41,210
- Look.
- Be a bit more reliable.

193
00:10:41,420 --> 00:10:43,180
Actually, Xiuya, I feel that

194
00:10:45,060 --> 00:10:46,780
if we stand from
the parents' perspective

195
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:47,940
to look at this matter,

196
00:10:47,940 --> 00:10:50,780
it's just that parents hope
we live well,

197
00:10:50,780 --> 00:10:52,380
stable, and happy.

198
00:10:52,380 --> 00:10:55,300
She thinks that if
you don't follow her plan,

199
00:10:55,300 --> 00:10:56,780
you won't live well.

200
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:58,900
Actually, you just need to
change her mindset.

201
00:11:03,940 --> 00:11:04,780
Speak of the devil.

202
00:11:04,780 --> 00:11:05,620
(Mom)

203
00:11:07,060 --> 00:11:08,580
Zhiyong, turn off the music.

204
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:09,500
Why?

205
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:10,580
I'm at the company.

206
00:11:10,820 --> 00:11:11,660
Okay, at the company.

207
00:11:11,660 --> 00:11:12,660
Change to a hot song.

208
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:16,340
Hello, Mom.

209
00:11:16,900 --> 00:11:17,740
Ya,

210
00:11:18,900 --> 00:11:20,180
have you gone home?

211
00:11:21,060 --> 00:11:22,180
Are you off work?

212
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:25,060
Not yet, I'm working overtime.

213
00:11:25,300 --> 00:11:27,500
Working overtime? Till when?

214
00:11:27,940 --> 00:11:28,900
Have you eaten?

215
00:11:29,180 --> 00:11:30,180
Not yet.

216
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:32,060
In that case,

217
00:11:32,180 --> 00:11:33,580
I will come over to pick you up now

218
00:11:33,660 --> 00:11:35,060
and we can have a meal together.

219
00:11:35,580 --> 00:11:36,420
No, Mom,

220
00:11:36,420 --> 00:11:38,060
it's not necessary, Mom...

221
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:40,380
It's over.

222
00:11:41,420 --> 00:11:42,260
What happened?

223
00:11:42,510 --> 00:11:44,320
My mom is coming to
the company to pick me up.

224
00:11:48,060 --> 00:11:49,420
- Goodbye.
- It's over.

225
00:11:49,420 --> 00:11:50,260
No...

226
00:11:52,780 --> 00:11:53,620
She panicked.

227
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:54,470
Three,

228
00:11:55,780 --> 00:11:56,620
two,

229
00:11:57,540 --> 00:11:58,380
one.

230
00:12:00,060 --> 00:12:00,940
Wish you peace.

231
00:12:00,940 --> 00:12:01,960
Eat something if you're hungry.

232
00:12:06,420 --> 00:12:07,820
- Sir, we have arrived.
- Okay.

233
00:12:07,820 --> 00:12:08,660
Take it slow.

234
00:12:08,670 --> 00:12:09,510
Okay.

235
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:10,980
Shall we go?

236
00:12:11,060 --> 00:12:11,900
Let's go.

237
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,420
Hello, where are you going?

238
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,180
Here, my daughter's company.

239
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:21,580
I'm picking her up for dinner.

240
00:12:22,380 --> 00:12:23,220
Alright.

241
00:12:23,580 --> 00:12:24,420
Thank you.

242
00:12:31,900 --> 00:12:33,180
Sir, could you please hurry?

243
00:12:33,180 --> 00:12:34,420
It's really urgent.

244
00:12:34,420 --> 00:12:35,900
Could you please help?

245
00:12:36,010 --> 00:12:37,110
Just in time for the evening peak.

246
00:12:37,110 --> 00:12:38,960
They don't move.
Is it possible that I can fly?

247
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:42,180
Look. Didn't that car just pass by?

248
00:12:42,180 --> 00:12:44,010
Let's move a little bit.

249
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:44,940
Be a bit more proactive.

250
00:12:44,940 --> 00:12:46,580
How about I let you drive?

251
00:13:05,180 --> 00:13:06,180
It's really congested.

252
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:08,060
Just in time for the evening peak.

253
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,940
But this road is still okay.

254
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:11,420
We'll be there soon.

255
00:13:14,060 --> 00:13:15,180
Hello? Jing,

256
00:13:15,860 --> 00:13:17,180
come downstairs right now, please.

257
00:13:18,060 --> 00:13:19,180
Yes, there's no time.

258
00:13:28,800 --> 00:13:29,660
Not there yet.

259
00:13:29,660 --> 00:13:31,500
Of course, I know
what your mom looks like.

260
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:33,420
Last time, we even
had dinner together.

261
00:13:33,420 --> 00:13:34,580
Stall her.

262
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:35,660
I'll be there soon.

263
00:13:36,380 --> 00:13:39,060
Stall her? How am
I supposed to stall her?

264
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:40,380
She's coming.

265
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:42,060
I've paid the money for you.

266
00:13:42,180 --> 00:13:43,060
Alright.

267
00:13:43,780 --> 00:13:44,620
Auntie,

268
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:46,940
I'm Xiuya's colleague.

269
00:13:46,940 --> 00:13:48,580
We met last time you came.

270
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:50,060
You're here to see Xiuya, right?

271
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:52,420
She's currently in a meeting
with the leader.

272
00:13:52,900 --> 00:13:53,740
Is that so?

273
00:13:54,060 --> 00:13:55,180
You're Jing, aren't you?

274
00:13:55,780 --> 00:13:56,660
My daughter's friend.

275
00:13:58,380 --> 00:13:59,420
You are all so busy.

276
00:13:59,610 --> 00:14:00,520
Yes, indeed.

277
00:14:00,580 --> 00:14:02,580
That's perfect. I'll go up with you.

278
00:14:03,500 --> 00:14:04,580
You don't need to worry about me.

279
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:06,940
I just need to find a place to sit.

280
00:14:06,940 --> 00:14:08,500
I won't delay your work, okay?

281
00:14:09,940 --> 00:14:11,060
The elevator is in this area.

282
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:13,900
My memory isn't bad, right?

283
00:14:14,900 --> 00:14:17,180
Auntie, do you need to go to the toilet?

284
00:14:17,180 --> 00:14:18,820
- I don't need it.
- You need it!

285
00:14:20,060 --> 00:14:21,900
The toilet upstairs is broken.

286
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:23,180
The meeting will take a long time.

287
00:14:23,180 --> 00:14:24,500
Why not go to one first?

288
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,010
It's okay. I don't have to.

289
00:14:26,010 --> 00:14:26,920
I really don't need it.

290
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:27,940
- Auntie, let's go.
- No need.

291
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:29,060
I actually want to go too.

292
00:14:29,060 --> 00:14:30,390
- Let's go together.
- I don't have to.

293
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:31,900
It really takes a long time to wait.

294
00:14:31,900 --> 00:14:33,940
- Do I have to go now?
- Go ahead. I'll carry the bag for you.

295
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:04,940
Sorry!

296
00:15:06,420 --> 00:15:07,260
Sorry.

297
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:11,500
You must have an upset stomach, right?

298
00:15:12,360 --> 00:15:13,520
You should take some medicine.

299
00:15:14,420 --> 00:15:15,820
Yeah.

300
00:15:20,060 --> 00:15:20,900
Mom.

301
00:15:21,500 --> 00:15:22,340
Xiuya?

302
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,940
We just mentioned you were in a meeting,

303
00:15:24,940 --> 00:15:26,380
and now it's over?

304
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:27,980
I was afraid you'd wait too long.

305
00:15:28,180 --> 00:15:29,300
I'm not afraid of waiting.

306
00:15:29,540 --> 00:15:31,580
A young girl shouldn't be
in such a rush.

307
00:15:31,580 --> 00:15:32,580
Let's hurry home.

308
00:15:32,580 --> 00:15:33,580
I'll call a car.

309
00:15:33,580 --> 00:15:35,090
- We're going back now?
- Yes, indeed.

310
00:15:35,090 --> 00:15:37,820
I'd like to see your office upstairs.

311
00:15:38,380 --> 00:15:39,940
There's nothing much to see.

312
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:45,140
Xiuya?

313
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:46,340
Xiuya,

314
00:15:46,350 --> 00:15:47,380
why did you come back?

315
00:15:48,420 --> 00:15:51,060
I left in a hurry and forgot something.

316
00:15:51,060 --> 00:15:52,260
Is it that water bottle?

317
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:54,500
Ma Chao said you must have
forgotten to come back for it.

318
00:15:54,500 --> 00:15:55,540
Luckily, I kept it for you.

319
00:15:55,540 --> 00:15:56,380
Look these words.

320
00:15:56,380 --> 00:15:57,900
Wasn't it me who asked you
to keep it for her?

321
00:15:58,180 --> 00:15:59,060
Thank you all.

322
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:00,680
I'll come back another day to get it.

323
00:16:00,680 --> 00:16:02,010
I have things to do,
so I'll leave first.

324
00:16:02,010 --> 00:16:03,580
- Mom, let's go.
- Is this Auntie?

325
00:16:04,380 --> 00:16:05,660
Hello Auntie, I am...

326
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:07,860
This is Ma Chao, and this is He Xiaoli,

327
00:16:07,860 --> 00:16:09,610
from the Corporate Communication
Department.

328
00:16:10,300 --> 00:16:11,420
Hello, everyone.

329
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:12,940
I am Ya's mom.

330
00:16:12,940 --> 00:16:14,800
Thank you for taking care of Ya.

331
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,900
We didn't take good care of her...

332
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:17,380
You're taking good care of me.

333
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:18,500
Mom, let's go.

334
00:16:19,580 --> 00:16:22,660
How about we treat everyone to a meal?

335
00:16:22,710 --> 00:16:23,620
- Sure!
- Sounds good!

336
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:26,060
Let's skip it for today.

337
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:27,500
They still have jobs.

338
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:28,370
No more jobs.

339
00:16:28,370 --> 00:16:30,280
We just finished interviewing
at the Foreign Trade Branch.

340
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:34,380
Hu seemed to say she had
something to discuss with you.

341
00:16:34,380 --> 00:16:36,660
Hu? Overtime again?

342
00:16:39,540 --> 00:16:41,060
Why is there something again?

343
00:16:41,060 --> 00:16:42,180
It used to be your job alone.

344
00:16:42,180 --> 00:16:43,420
Now it takes the three of us to do it.

345
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:44,660
Mom, the car has arrived.

346
00:16:44,660 --> 00:16:46,420
Let's not keep the driver
waiting too long.

347
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:47,740
We're leaving now.

348
00:16:48,060 --> 00:16:49,780
Let's have a meal together another day.

349
00:16:49,780 --> 00:16:51,380
Alright, bye.

350
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:54,180
Having a wealthy boyfriend
really makes a difference.

351
00:16:54,180 --> 00:16:55,500
What she's wearing may look plain,

352
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,940
but it's the designer brand.

353
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,900
Did Hu mention anything?

354
00:17:02,940 --> 00:17:04,500
I'll go to the toilet first.

355
00:17:06,340 --> 00:17:07,220
What's going on?

356
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:08,460
Let's go.

357
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:11,060
Go work overtime.

358
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,300
- Take another menu.
- Sure.

359
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:16,460
Mom, is this what you call
a casual meal?

360
00:17:17,540 --> 00:17:19,500
I checked online and saw this restaurant

361
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,580
has great reviews.

362
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:23,100
It is indeed quite good.

363
00:17:25,060 --> 00:17:26,340
Are there any recommended dishes?

364
00:17:26,340 --> 00:17:27,700
Yes, take a look at this.

365
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:29,740
Pepper Deep Sea Live Croaker
of Peach Blossom Island

366
00:17:30,220 --> 00:17:32,520
(798 yuan per jin)
It is our signature East Sea seafood.

367
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:33,860
(Original price 798 yuan per jin,
Member price 768 yuan per jin)

368
00:17:33,860 --> 00:17:35,340
Then let's have one portion of this.

369
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:38,110
I suggest the two of you order more
than two jin of live croaker.

370
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:39,580
Alright, then more than two jin.

371
00:17:39,580 --> 00:17:40,420
Okay.

372
00:17:41,220 --> 00:17:43,820
I suggest you also order
two portions of this.

373
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:45,780
Kalimantan Freshly Stewed Cubilose.

374
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:47,780
Cubilose?

375
00:17:48,060 --> 00:17:49,300
Okay, two portions.

376
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:51,220
No, Mom.

377
00:17:51,220 --> 00:17:53,500
I won't eat it.
You can have it yourself.

378
00:17:53,580 --> 00:17:55,580
Come on. It's good for women.

379
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:56,780
Two portions, please.

380
00:17:56,780 --> 00:17:57,620
Alright.

381
00:17:59,500 --> 00:18:00,580
Let's have this one too.

382
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:01,420
Okay.

383
00:18:05,860 --> 00:18:06,700
And this one.

384
00:18:07,340 --> 00:18:08,580
Make sure it's not too spicy.

385
00:18:08,580 --> 00:18:09,630
- Mildly spicy.
- Alright.

386
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:11,240
And add some staple food.

387
00:18:12,860 --> 00:18:15,340
Let me repeat the menu for you two.

388
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:18,240
Pepper Deep Sea Live Croaker
of Peach Blossom Island,

389
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:20,480
and Authentic Kalimantan Freshly
Stewed Cubilose for two.

390
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,520
Ginger Sauce Chinese Broccoli,
and Exquisite Five Flavor Dish.

391
00:18:23,580 --> 00:18:25,580
- Okay.
- Is that too much

392
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,220
for the two of us?

393
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:29,580
Our restaurant is a
creative concept restaurant.

394
00:18:29,580 --> 00:18:31,220
The portion sizes are not very large.

395
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:33,060
Alright, no problem.

396
00:18:33,060 --> 00:18:34,060
If we can't finish, just left.

397
00:18:34,060 --> 00:18:35,570
You don't need the menu anymore, right?

398
00:18:35,570 --> 00:18:36,410
No need.

399
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,540
Please wait a moment.

400
00:18:40,580 --> 00:18:41,420
Have some tea.

401
00:18:47,780 --> 00:18:49,860
Just a simple word: preparation.

402
00:18:50,100 --> 00:18:52,300
First, test Auntie's attitude.

403
00:18:52,300 --> 00:18:54,580
Just say your colleague,

404
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:56,860
a certain colleague,

405
00:18:57,060 --> 00:18:59,100
who suffered silent treatment
at the company.

406
00:18:59,280 --> 00:19:00,660
He can't take it and he's quitting.

407
00:19:00,860 --> 00:19:03,020
See what Auntie's attitude is
when she hears this.

408
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:08,100
Mom, a friend of mine resigned recently.

409
00:19:08,540 --> 00:19:09,860
Who? Which one?

410
00:19:10,540 --> 00:19:11,380
Xiaolan.

411
00:19:12,580 --> 00:19:13,420
Xiaolan?

412
00:19:14,060 --> 00:19:15,300
I was going to ask you about it.

413
00:19:15,340 --> 00:19:17,580
Didn't Xiaolan go abroad?

414
00:19:17,860 --> 00:19:18,820
She's back

415
00:19:18,820 --> 00:19:19,860
and found a job now, right?

416
00:19:20,580 --> 00:19:23,380
Yeah, she thinks it's better
to go back here to find a job.

417
00:19:23,540 --> 00:19:25,060
Then why did she resign again?

418
00:19:26,060 --> 00:19:28,020
Her previous job

419
00:19:28,260 --> 00:19:30,620
was not quite aligned with
her future development goals.

420
00:19:31,030 --> 00:19:32,860
Also, she didn't get along well
with her boss.

421
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:34,060
So she resigned.

422
00:19:36,860 --> 00:19:38,300
Xiaolan

423
00:19:38,340 --> 00:19:39,860
is from a wealthy family

424
00:19:40,200 --> 00:19:42,860
and thinks herself above her business.

425
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:45,300
Whatever she does,
she is also inconsistent.

426
00:19:46,220 --> 00:19:47,580
However, since she resigned,

427
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:49,300
you should support her more.

428
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:53,020
But I think her resignation
is quite good.

429
00:19:53,020 --> 00:19:54,540
She doesn't have to endure
grievances anymore.

430
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:56,100
Moreover, I think
the most important thing is

431
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,300
that we must find a job we like.

432
00:19:58,540 --> 00:19:59,580
So said the words.

433
00:20:00,260 --> 00:20:02,420
But if you resign just
because of a little frustration,

434
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:04,580
then there will be no job to do.

435
00:20:08,340 --> 00:20:09,820
You kids

436
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:12,540
always aim too high.

437
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,540
How can you find a job

438
00:20:14,540 --> 00:20:16,580
you really like now?

439
00:20:17,260 --> 00:20:20,380
Finding a job with a decent salary
is already good enough.

440
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:23,860
For example, to enter your workplace,

441
00:20:24,260 --> 00:20:27,060
didn't you take the test
several times

442
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:28,340
before you finally got in?

443
00:20:28,820 --> 00:20:29,860
And then there's Zheng Hao,

444
00:20:30,340 --> 00:20:32,860
who is the sales champion every year.

445
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:36,580
I feel quite happy
just thinking about these things.

446
00:20:37,100 --> 00:20:38,580
I think my daughter

447
00:20:38,780 --> 00:20:40,260
really doesn't make me worry.

448
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:49,060
Hello, Table 12 is ready to pay.

449
00:20:52,060 --> 00:20:53,820
Is there any discount available?

450
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:55,860
Sorry, there are no discounts
at the moment.

451
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,960
You can register for member points.

452
00:20:57,960 --> 00:21:00,190
One point per yuan can be redeemed
for gifts at the end of the year.

453
00:21:00,620 --> 00:21:01,580
What gifts?

454
00:21:02,060 --> 00:21:03,020
5,000 points

455
00:21:03,020 --> 00:21:05,260
can redeem for a carbon fiber umbrella.

456
00:21:05,260 --> 00:21:07,340
10,000 points can redeem
for an aromatherapy product.

457
00:21:07,340 --> 00:21:08,620
And 30,000 points...

458
00:21:08,620 --> 00:21:11,060
Sorry, I just wanted to ask
if there are any discounts.

459
00:21:11,380 --> 00:21:13,260
Sorry, there aren't any at the moment.

460
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:15,540
Can I use Ant Credit Pay?

461
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:16,700
Yes, you can.

462
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,060
What's wrong, Mom?

463
00:21:24,060 --> 00:21:24,900
Why don't you eat?

464
00:21:25,540 --> 00:21:26,380
Is it not tasty?

465
00:21:26,860 --> 00:21:28,620
I'm waiting for you.

466
00:21:32,060 --> 00:21:33,300
Zheng Hao is on a business trip?

467
00:21:34,580 --> 00:21:35,580
When will he be back?

468
00:21:36,170 --> 00:21:38,860
How about we meet his parents first?

469
00:21:40,300 --> 00:21:42,060
He will be back in a few days.

470
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:44,060
Let's wait until he comes back.

471
00:21:45,860 --> 00:21:49,060
However, it's not appropriate to meet
his parents on the spur of the moment.

472
00:21:49,340 --> 00:21:50,620
You've been dragging this out

473
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:52,540
with Zheng Hao for so long.

474
00:21:52,540 --> 00:21:54,260
Let's arrange to meet his parents.

475
00:21:54,260 --> 00:21:55,860
Your dad and I will meet them.

476
00:21:56,780 --> 00:21:58,300
If your affairs are in order,

477
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,820
I'll fulfill my wish.

478
00:22:02,860 --> 00:22:03,740
Mom,

479
00:22:03,810 --> 00:22:05,340
is your daughter unable to get married,

480
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:06,180
or what is it?

481
00:22:06,180 --> 00:22:07,260
Why are you in such a hurry?

482
00:22:07,580 --> 00:22:08,820
No, that's not it.

483
00:22:10,100 --> 00:22:13,540
I feel like you're getting older.

484
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:16,540
Alright, I know.

485
00:22:16,540 --> 00:22:17,380
Hurry up and eat.

486
00:22:18,100 --> 00:22:20,580
Let me get you some vegetables
and some fish.

487
00:22:23,860 --> 00:22:26,060
Waiter, check for Table 12.

488
00:22:26,460 --> 00:22:27,620
Hello, it's already been paid.

489
00:22:29,060 --> 00:22:31,020
How could I let you
spend money here?

490
00:22:31,560 --> 00:22:33,910
Alright, I'll just take advantage of
my daughter's benefits.

491
00:22:33,910 --> 00:22:34,820
Absolutely.

492
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:36,100
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

493
00:22:37,380 --> 00:22:39,300
There are so many
styles of clothes here.

494
00:22:40,580 --> 00:22:41,820
The quality is also quite good.

495
00:22:44,820 --> 00:22:46,620
This kind of white shirt,

496
00:22:46,620 --> 00:22:48,020
you could use it for work.

497
00:22:48,540 --> 00:22:50,340
The quality is really good, right?

498
00:22:51,580 --> 00:22:52,420
Isn't it?

499
00:22:52,860 --> 00:22:54,300
Sister, you have a great eye.

500
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,260
This shirt is made of mulberry silk.

501
00:22:56,270 --> 00:22:58,080
It's very comfortable to wear.
Why don't you try it on?

502
00:22:58,260 --> 00:22:59,890
Not me, I want to buy it
for my daughter.

503
00:22:59,890 --> 00:23:01,100
She can use it for work.

504
00:23:01,340 --> 00:23:02,580
Let's take a look over here.

505
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:03,580
In our store,

506
00:23:03,580 --> 00:23:05,440
